content: Younger musicians inspired by Elton John include which British artist who collaborated with him on the song 'Don't Go Breaking My Heart'?

Elton John has inspired numerous younger musicians across various genres. One notable British artist who collaborated with him is Kiki Dee. Together, they recorded the iconic duet "Don't Go Breaking My Heart," which was released in 1976 and became a massive hit worldwide. This collaboration not only showcased their vocal chemistry but also highlighted Elton John's influence on emerging artists of that time.
